704076f-b.title: Brooklyn: Elderts Lane - Jamaica Avenue
704076f-b.text:
(1)
Elderts Lane, at the S.W. corner of Jamaica Ave., showing Dan Cobb's
grocery store at what is now (1929) 1004 Jamaica Ave. This structure
was erected on Ackerly's ground. It was conducted as a store by
Daniel Cobb from 1850 (2) to 1860. It is not a store on the maps of
1873. The building was demolished in April 1925. a 1-story garage oc-
oupies the site. (at present (1937).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing a Jamaica Ave., view.
August 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, facing Jamaica Ave.,overhead is the Fulton Street Eleva-
ted line of the B.M.T.
Anril 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
